last_episode_to_air.name: Wiener
last_episode_to_air.overview: Pinky tries to repress his wienerness when he's told that only human boys and girls can compete in the Ultimate Mascot Championship.

name: Pinky Malinky
overview: Pinky Malinky sees the bright side of everything, including being born a hot dog. With his BFFs in tow, this little wiener takes a bite out of life.

seasons.name: Part 1
seasons.overview: Pinky Malinky sees the bright side of everything, including being born a hot dog. With his BFFs in tow, this little wiener takes a bite out of life.

seasons.name: Part 2
seasons.overview: Pinky Malinky is on a roll! Catch up on this joyful hot dog boy's continuing adventures as he spreads fun and positivity with best friends Babs and JJ.

seasons.name: Part 3
seasons.overview: Pinky Malinky isn't the type of hot dog boy who sits around on his buns, and with his BFFs Babs and JJ, he's learning how to relish the little things.

episodes.name: Snack
episodes.overview: When the town's favorite treat gets discontinued, Pinky attempts to reverse-engineer the recipe to avert a Snackpocalypse.

episodes.name: Pet
episodes.overview: While volunteering at the animal shelter, Pinky takes a shine to a ferocious feline and decides they're going to be meow-velous together.

episodes.name: Tech
episodes.overview: Worried that his mom isn't using the latest technology, Pinky shows her how to get RIPPED: really, insanely, pretty prepared to engage with digital.

episodes.name: Spirit
episodes.overview: No one relishes school spirit week more than Pinky. But in his zeal to boost the mood of head cheerleader Tina, he doesn't see she has a crush on him.

episodes.name: Hater
episodes.overview: Pinky loves Sackenhack, so he's shocked when someone gives his online posts about the town a thumbs down. Can he change the mind of this Sacken-hater?

episodes.name: Video
episodes.overview: Pinky, Babs and JJ make a hilarious video that's “almost perfect,” a so-so assessment that doesn't cut the mustard for perfectionist Pinky.

episodes.name: Duck
episodes.overview: When the town's largest duck dies, Pinky makes it his mission to convince everyone that King Sackenquack is still alive.

episodes.name: Mannequin
episodes.overview: JJ's dream of being featured on a fashion blog goes awry when the outfit he adores doesn't fit. Enter the sausage stylist with an idea …

episodes.name: Secret
episodes.overview: When JJ and Babs mock a TV show Pinky loves, he starts lying -- and breaking school rules -- to binge-watch the episodes in secret.

episodes.name: Scary
episodes.overview: Pinky and Babs discover JJ doesn't like scary movies, so they concoct a plan to get him over his fears by scaring “the scared” out of him. Eeeeeeek!

episodes.name: Book
episodes.overview: Pinky tries to sneak a book on extreme chimney sweeping back into the library after he forgets to check it out. To be frank, it doesn't go well.

episodes.name: Team
episodes.overview: Armed with some doggedly creative plays, Pinky joins the school football team with one goal in mind: to get them their first win.

episodes.name: Game
episodes.overview: JJ buys a new leather jacket and makes plans to do more “extreme” stuff, causing Pinky to fret about the future of their weekly role-playing game.

episodes.name: Undercover
episodes.overview: Pinky cooks up an undercover scheme to save Bob's security guard job after he screws up a safety demonstration at school.

episodes.name: Fun
episodes.overview: After misbehaving in class, Pinky uses his trip to Principal Pfunne's office to help her come out of her very rigid shell.

episodes.name: Brother
episodes.overview: When JJ accidentally calls Pinky's mother “Mom,” the little wiener has an amazing idea: They should go from friends ... to brothers.

episodes.name: Sensei
episodes.overview: To reawaken Coach Freebird's love of teaching (or maybe just awaken it, period), Pinky joins his tae kwon do club and vows to be the perfect student.

episodes.name: Hangout
episodes.overview: A termite infestation forces Pinky, Babs and JJ to hunt for a new hangout spot. But nothing's good enough for the hard-to-please hot dog.

episodes.name: Sock
episodes.overview: A misplaced sock ignites an avalanche of worry for Pinky, who strongly believes all pairs should stay together for life.

episodes.name: Count
episodes.overview: An app that counts steps prompts Pinky, Babs and JJ to add up every single thing they do. Competition's good for friendship, right?

episodes.name: Voice
episodes.overview: After discovering that his life's purpose is to inspire people, Pinky sets out to perfect a new voice for his oral report.

episodes.name: Phone
episodes.overview: Pinky suspects his phone is out to get him when his texts to Babs autocorrect into insults. His solution? Be his own phone to find her and apologize.

episodes.name: Friend
episodes.overview: Pinky deals with jealous feelings when he finds out about Babs's onetime pal, Jules. Learning your best friend had a BFF before you is the wurst!

episodes.name: Gym
episodes.overview: Things get out of hand when Pinky wrongly assumes his mom is training him to take over her successful half-gym, half-bakery business.

episodes.name: List
episodes.overview: Pinky and JJ hear that Babs is moving, so they try to make their last night together special. Good thing they've got Pinky's beefy Babs bucket list.

episodes.name: Double
episodes.overview: When Pinky's report card shows an absence, he attempts to erase it -- and save his permanent record -- by living two days simultaneously.

episodes.name: Sight
episodes.overview: Babs temporarily loses her sight after a trip to the eye doctor, inspiring Pinky to become her guide hot dog.

episodes.name: Grounded
episodes.overview: In his excitement over family movie night, Pinky accidentally breaks his mom's trophy, then feels guilty and decides to ground himself.

1.name: Part 1
1.overview: Pinky Malinky sees the bright side of everything, including being born a hot dog. With his BFFs in tow, this little wiener takes a bite out of life.

episodes.name: Money
episodes.overview: After finding a $100 bill on the ground, Pinky, Babs and JJ go on a spending spree without stopping to consider the consequences.

episodes.name: Babs
episodes.overview: Pinky's upset when he doesn't know Babs's favorite kind of cupcake, so he steps up his best-friend game by learning everything he can about her.

episodes.name: Sarcasm
episodes.overview: Hoping to become a more well-rounded hot dog, Pinky seeks out an expert in sarcasm and asks her to be his coach.

episodes.name: Song
episodes.overview: Pinky, Babs and JJ share a magical moment when they hear a catchy tune on the radio, only to run into trouble when they try and track it down.

episodes.name: Brain
episodes.overview: When Pinky forgets an important anniversary, he decides to delete unwanted memories from his brain in order to make room for new ones.

episodes.name: Trophy
episodes.overview: Pinky embarks on a positivity campaign to boost student morale -- armed with a lot of gold stars. But the plan backfires by working a bit too well.

episodes.name: Search
episodes.overview: When an online search of his name turns up a page full of falsehoods, Pinky attempts to do everything listed so he won't get caught living a lie.

episodes.name: Haircut
episodes.overview: JJ goes into hiding over a tragic haircut, prompting Pinky and Babs to try and lift his spirits by looking as terrible as they can.

episodes.name: Crutch
episodes.overview: Pinky fakes an injury to help bring out the best in everyone -- but he takes it too far. (And Pinky finally reveals why he has a bandage on his head!)

episodes.name: Smile
episodes.overview: Pinky gets a job bagging groceries. But when a customer leaves the store without smiling, the hard-working wiener has a tough time letting it go.

episodes.name: Cranky
episodes.overview: When Pinky wakes up on the wrong side of bed, he figures the best way to overcome his grumpiness is to face the day with a big smile.

episodes.name: Weeds
episodes.overview: Pinky's thrilled that his dad is finally letting him help in the garden. But he grows uneasy when he learns that certain types of plants aren't welcome.

episodes.name: Advanced
episodes.overview: JJ's nervousness around new people threatens to get the best of him when he's accepted into an "advanced" class at school.

episodes.name: Bestie
episodes.overview: Dumbfounded when he discovers that his dad doesn't have a best friend, Pinky launches a search to find him a BFF.

episodes.name: King
episodes.overview: Pinky holds a series of challenges inspired by his favorite TV show, "Quest of Crowns," to decide who will reign as king at the school dance.

episodes.name: Pinky
episodes.overview: Hoping to raise school spirit and make dreams come true, Pinky encourages his classmates to elect him mascot -- and promises the impossible in return.

2.name: Part 2
2.overview: Pinky Malinky is on a roll! Catch up on this joyful hot dog boy's continuing adventures as he spreads fun and positivity with best friends Babs and JJ.

episodes.name: Change
episodes.overview: Pinky's unhappy when his favorite stop sign gets a high-tech replacement, so he sets out to save all the things he loves in Sackenhack.

episodes.name: Outdoors
episodes.overview: What begins as a fun way for Pinky and Babs to boost their chances of earning a SackenScout badge quickly spirals into a heated competition.

episodes.name: Spotlight
episodes.overview: Determined to prove that Babs and JJ are more than just "supporting characters," Pinky pushes them out of his shadow -- and into the limelight.

episodes.name: Dog
episodes.overview: When Mr. Dog isn't feeling well, Babs needs an assist from Pinky and JJ to get the pooch to the vet without Bob finding out.

episodes.name: Birthday
episodes.overview: Bob gets stuck working a security shift at the mall during his planned birthday bash. But Pinky makes sure his pal still has a chance to party.

episodes.name: Individual
episodes.overview: After the school's troublemaker confesses he's no good at being bad, Pinky offers to help him figure out who he really is.

episodes.name: Dinner
episodes.overview: In an effort to get his busy parents to reconnect as a couple, Pinky arranges a romantic dinner for two.

episodes.name: Clique
episodes.overview: Pinky's concerned he's excluding others by hanging out with just Babs and JJ, so he invites everyone to join in on the trio's after-school activities.

episodes.name: Fundraiser
episodes.overview: On the eve of the annual fun run, Babs is once again without a sponsor, so Pinky vows to do everything he can to find her one. And he means everything.

episodes.name: Man
episodes.overview: After finding a hair on his face, Pinky concludes he should be the new man of the house -- a decision that leaves his dad at loose ends.

episodes.name: Wrestling
episodes.overview: When Principal Pfunne threatens to turn the students' laid-back gym class into a boot camp, Pinky suggests they learn tag-team wrestling instead.

episodes.name: Eraser
episodes.overview: Worried that his beloved eraser is becoming too small to wipe out his mistakes, Pinky commits to living the rest of his life error-free.

episodes.name: Dreams
episodes.overview: Pinky hatches a plan to make his parents famous after learning they once performed together as a singing duo.

episodes.name: Spark
episodes.overview: Convinced that his friendship with Babs and JJ is in crisis, Pinky turns to a relationship app to help them get their spark back.

episodes.name: Wiener
episodes.overview: Pinky tries to repress his wienerness when he's told that only human boys and girls can compete in the Ultimate Mascot Championship.

3.name: Part 3
3.overview: Pinky Malinky isn't the type of hot dog boy who sits around on his buns, and with his BFFs Babs and JJ, he's learning how to relish the little things.
